I really liked The Quest and as soon as I finished it, I bought this expansion. But was quite disappointed. It is decent but unlike the original game, there is much less exploration since the map feels empty and lacks interest. I frequently found myself walking along large portions of map with nothing relevant in them. No caves to explore, characters to talk to. Quests are too simple and not very interesting. Still, I will play the other expansions. Already bought Celtic Rift and I must say It's so much better. So far, great map, a lot to explore and many missions.
This game is very easy to play.

Wonderful to finally have access to this game on Android.  the upgraded graphics are very welcome.  While there are misogynistic elements I never liked in the original game, I won't take stars away.  Thanks for porting this game and I look forward to new work from Redshift.

replyContent: You have to enable the expansion. Start the expansion app then select "Enable in The Quest". The Quest will then start and will notify you of the successful enabling (The "Islands of Ice and Fire" expansion has been enabled. ...). After that you can travel to the expansion areas by talking to Captain Hanty in Mithria harbor.

content: The expansion is finally here and it is amazing so far! It's been a long and agonizing week for me since beating The Quest lol. So thank you Sylon and Elendil for all the hard work you've put in for us android users :)

Loved the original game but this add on felt tacky. Like the original game, you can't finish certain quests because of your build. That is a good way to give replay and a vital part of in depth RPGs. Unfortunately the add on makes large strings of quests unbeatable from this aspect and just leaves a mess in your quest log book. I won't be finishing this add on.
